		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.56]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>AE kiting for bards is gone, unless you take advantage of bad geometry/collision detection in some very particular areas, which would be considered an exploit. The way our AEs work now:<br /><br />If a mob WANTS to move (meaning he can be rooted and this still applies, because he wants to move, just can't) then he will not take any damage from our AEs. Any other effects, ie, snare/slow/debuff will still land. There is no reduction in range of our AE's. That was their initial intent, but that got changed to it's current form.<br /><br />As far as playing a bard, I love my bard and he's still my main. I never really liked AEing though, so it really wasn't a big loss to me. For tips on twisting, song selection, etc, go to the bard class discussion area linked on the left here, and check out <a href="HTTP://www.eqdiva.com" target="akztarg">EQDiva</a>.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062&resize=true" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866&resize=true" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" target="akztarg">The Firestormers</a></span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006061&resize=true" target="akztarg">Zolotaya</a> - <span class="sm">Ms Necro</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189723" target="akztarg">Zeibis</a> - <span class="sm">Monk<